main event: A large unidentified flying object was sighted hovering over Arcata Bay in Arcata, California on April 6, 1960.
interesting points: The object appeared to be oval-shaped, measuring approximately 25-30 feet in diameter.
The object was glowing brightly and emitting rays of light.
After hovering for several minutes, the object accelerated rapidly and disappeared from sight within seconds.
The report includes a photograph of the moon, as well as two photographs of unidentified objects, one elongated in shape and the other a large oval-shaped object.
The case remains open due to insufficient information to evaluate the report.
sighted object: a large, oval-shaped unidentified flying object
